This paper discusses the energy efficiency of cellular wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication in computer science. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses potential improvements at the physical layer and higher layers of the communication protocol hierarchy, which falls under the category of information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses multi-tier networks and exploiting mobility patterns, which falls under the category of control and systems engineering, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the Carbon footprint of cellular wireless networks, which falls under the category of cybersecurity and privacy, making cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses potential methods to reduce energy inefficiency, which falls under the category of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
